# API Routes

## Structure

- Route handlers in `src/app/api/**/route.ts`
- Export named `GET`, `POST`, `PATCH`, `DELETE` as needed
- Return `NextResponse.json()` with appropriate status codes

## Auth

- Read session: `getSession()` from `@/lib/auth/session`
- Login/signup attach cookie via `attachSessionCookie(response, token)`
- Maker-only routes: `requireMakerUser()` from `@/lib/maker/require-maker`
  - Returns `null` → respond with `unauthorized()` (401)
  - User must have `role === "maker"` and linked `maker`

## Validation

- Type-guard request body with `isXBody(body: unknown): body is X` functions
- Trim strings; validate ranges server-side (don't trust client)
- Geocode addresses before saving maker location

## Prisma

- Use shared client: `import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma"`
- Map DB records to API types via `mapPrisma*` helpers in `src/lib/`
- Include relations explicitly (`filaments`, `maker`) when needed

## Orders

- Enforce `maker.status === "available"` and `minOrderPriceCzk` on create
- Delivery: `pickup` (price 0) or `zasilkovna` (stub quote in `src/lib/delivery/zasilkovna.ts`)

## Errors

```typescript
// ✅ Pattern
try {
  // ...
} catch (error) {
  console.error("[POST /api/...]", error);
  return NextResponse.json({ error: "Human message" }, { status: 500 });
}
```
